title: The Marquis of Anaon (Scanlation)
description:
T01-T05 of 'The Marquis of Anaon'

Darquad, 2002-2008, 52-56 pages each

Written by Fabien Vehlmann

Illustrated by Matthieu Bonhomme

Colored by Delf

The Isle of Brac 
Black Virgin
Providence
The Beast
The Chamber of Cheops

With apologies, I don't know what this is about. I came across it looking for issues of 'The Marquis', by Guy Davis, and since I didn't see it here at TPB I thought I'd go ahead and share it. It seems to be set sometime in the late 1700s or early 1800s and the art is quite good. A couple of issues deal with clipper ships and sea travel and it seems, in general, to be about one man who does a good deal of getting around (I'm guessing he's the Marquis of Anaon).
